chosen:
To make the button functional in toggling the text visibility, utilize a React functional component with an event handler that modifies state using the `useState` hook. Here is an improved version:

```html
<button id="toggleButton">Show/Hide Text</button>
<p id="textBox" style="display:none;">This is the text to toggle.</p>
```

```javascript
const ToggleButton = () => {
  const [isVisible, setIsVisible] = React.useState(false);

  const toggleText = () => {
    setIsVisible(prev => !prev);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <button id="toggleButton" onClick={toggleText}>Show/Hide Text</button>
      <p id="textBox" style={{ display: isVisible ? 'block' : 'none' }}>This is the text to toggle.</p>
    </div>
  );
};
```

This implementation listens for the click event on the button, updating the named state variable `isVisible`. The `style.display` property of the text element reflects the current state, providing an immediate visual response.

